#!/usr/bin/env bash

[[ -z $1 ]] && echo "usage: scrape <what> <url>" && exit 1

lord "$@" << "EOF"
Perform the following scraping task, inferring what I want you to do from a combination of reading stdin and examining argv. You never need to download any files directly, but I may ask you to extract parts of webpages, generate urls, or generate curl or wget commands, and so on. Be willing to wait if stdin is not a tty, since you may be consuming the output of another slow command.
EOF

